  "title": "Director (Institutional & Insurance Capital Raising)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Lead fundraising initiatives targeting insurance companies, pension funds, endowments, foundations, institutional family offices, reinsurers, and balance-sheet investors.</li><li>Build and maintain strategic relationships with CIOs, alternatives heads, investment committees, and key decision-makers to secure anchor investments and cornerstone commitments.</li><li>Manage institutional due diligence, RFPs, and investment committee processes, coordinating internal teams to support investor inquiries and presentations.</li><li>Collaborate with the CIO and investment team to structure institutional-grade fund vehicles and integrate investor feedback into fund design, terms, and positioning.</li><li>Develop strategic partnerships with consultants, insurance platforms, and capital partners, supporting co-investment and bespoke mandate opportunities.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>At least 8 years of experience in <strong>institutional fundraising, private credit, or alternative investments.</strong></li><li>Demonstrated success in securing capital from <strong>institutional and insurance investors.</strong></li><li>Strong understanding of private credit, secured lending, and credit risk.</li><li>Excellent written, verbal, and presentation skills; comfortable engaging with senior stakeholders and investment committees.</li></ul><p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p><p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p><p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p><p>Registration: R21100996</p>",
